## 1. Introduction

### 1.1 Purpose
This Software Requirements Specification (SRS) document describes the functional and non-functional requirements for the AI Resume Generator Pro application. The document is intended for developers, testers, and stakeholders involved in the development and deployment of the system.

### 1.2 Scope
The AI Resume Generator Pro is a desktop application that assists users in creating professional resumes. The system provides two generation modes:
- **Template Mode**: Quick resume generation using predefined templates
- **AI Mode**: Intelligent resume generation using Google FLAN-T5 language model

The application operates entirely offline, ensuring user privacy and data security.

### 1.3 Definitions, Acronyms, and Abbreviations
- **SRS**: Software Requirements Specification
- **UI**: User Interface
- **AI**: Artificial Intelligence
- **PDF**: Portable Document Format
- **SQLite**: Lightweight relational database management system
- **FLAN-T5**: Fine-tuned LAnguage Net - Text-to-Text Transfer Transformer (Google's language model)
- **ML**: Machine Learning
- **NLP**: Natural Language Processing

### 1.4 References
- Python 3.12+ Documentation
- Tkinter GUI Library Documentation
- Transformers Library Documentation (Hugging Face)
- ReportLab PDF Generation Library
- SQLite Database Documentation

### 1.5 Overview
This document is organized into sections covering system description, functional requirements, interface requirements, non-functional requirements, and data management specifications.

---

## 2. Overall Description

### 2.1 Product Perspective
AI Resume Generator Pro is a standalone desktop application designed to operate independently without requiring internet connectivity. The system consists of:
- **Frontend**: Tkinter-based graphical user interface
- **Backend**: Python-based resume generation engine
- **Storage**: SQLite database for local data persistence
- **AI Component**: Optional transformers-based language model for AI-powered generation

### 2.2 Product Functions
The main functions of the system include:
- Generate professional resumes using templates or AI
- Save and load user input data
- Store generated resumes in a collection
- Export resumes to PDF format
- Provide an intuitive, modern user interface with custom theme

### 2.3 User Classes and Characteristics
**Primary Users**: Job seekers, professionals, students
- **Technical Expertise**: Basic computer literacy
- **Frequency of Use**: Occasional to frequent (depending on job search activity)
- **User Goals**: Create professional, well-formatted resumes quickly

### 2.4 Operating Environment
- **Operating System**: Windows, macOS, Linux (cross-platform)
- **Python Version**: 3.12 or higher
- **Display Resolution**: Minimum 950x750 pixels
- **Storage**: Minimum 500 MB free disk space (more if AI model is used)
- **RAM**: Minimum 4 GB (8 GB recommended for AI mode)

### 2.5 Design and Implementation Constraints
- Must operate offline without internet connectivity
- Must use Python and Tkinter for cross-platform compatibility
- AI model must be loaded locally
- Database must be lightweight (SQLite)
- UI must maintain specific color theme (pink, purple, lavender, mint)

### 2.6 Assumptions and Dependencies
**Assumptions:**
- Users have Python 3.12+ installed
- Users can install required Python packages
- Users have sufficient disk space for AI model (if used)

**Dependencies:**
- reportlab (PDF generation)
- transformers (AI model)
- torch (neural network framework)
- sentencepiece (tokenization)
- tkinter (UI framework - included with Python)

---

## 3. System Features

### 3.1 Resume Generation

#### 3.1.1 Template Mode Generation
**Priority**: High
**Description**: Generate resumes using predefined templates with smart formatting.

**Functional Requirements:**
- **REQ-3.1.1-1**: System shall accept user input fields: name, email, phone, education, skills, and experience
- **REQ-3.1.1-2**: System shall generate a formatted resume using template-based algorithms
- **REQ-3.1.1-3**: Generation shall complete within 2 seconds
- **REQ-3.1.1-4**: System shall display generated resume in the output text area
- **REQ-3.1.1-5**: System shall format education, skills, and experience sections appropriately

#### 3.1.2 AI Mode Generation
**Priority**: Medium
**Description**: Generate resumes using Google FLAN-T5 AI model for creative content generation.

**Functional Requirements:**
- **REQ-3.1.2-1**: System shall load the FLAN-T5-small model on first use
- **REQ-3.1.2-2**: System shall process user input through the AI model
- **REQ-3.1.2-3**: System shall generate creative resume content based on input
- **REQ-3.1.2-4**: System shall provide progress feedback during model loading
- **REQ-3.1.2-5**: System shall handle AI model unavailability gracefully
- **REQ-3.1.2-6**: AI generation may take 10-30 seconds depending on hardware

### 3.2 Data Persistence

#### 3.2.1 Save Input Data
**Priority**: High
**Description**: Allow users to save their input data for future reuse.

**Functional Requirements:**
- **REQ-3.2.1-1**: System shall validate that name field is not empty before saving
- **REQ-3.2.1-2**: System shall store input data in SQLite database
- **REQ-3.2.1-3**: System shall record timestamp of save operation
- **REQ-3.2.1-4**: System shall provide confirmation message after successful save
- **REQ-3.2.1-5**: System shall handle database errors gracefully

#### 3.2.2 Load Input Data
**Priority**: High
**Description**: Allow users to load previously saved input data.

**Functional Requirements:**
- **REQ-3.2.2-1**: System shall display list of saved input records
- **REQ-3.2.2-2**: Each record shall show name and timestamp
- **REQ-3.2.2-3**: System shall populate input fields with selected record data
- **REQ-3.2.2-4**: System shall handle empty database scenario
- **REQ-3.2.2-5**: System shall provide user-friendly selection interface

#### 3.2.3 Save Generated Resume
**Priority**: High
**Description**: Allow users to save generated resumes to a collection.

**Functional Requirements:**
- **REQ-3.2.3-1**: System shall prompt user for resume title
- **REQ-3.2.3-2**: System shall store complete resume content in database
- **REQ-3.2.3-3**: System shall record generation mode (Template/AI)
- **REQ-3.2.3-4**: System shall timestamp the saved resume
- **REQ-3.2.3-5**: System shall validate title is not empty

#### 3.2.4 Load Generated Resume
**Priority**: High
**Description**: Allow users to view previously saved resumes.

**Functional Requirements:**
- **REQ-3.2.4-1**: System shall display list of saved resumes with titles
- **REQ-3.2.4-2**: System shall show generation mode and timestamp for each resume
- **REQ-3.2.4-3**: System shall load selected resume into output area
- **REQ-3.2.4-4**: System shall handle empty collection scenario

### 3.3 PDF Export

#### 3.3.1 Export Resume to PDF
**Priority**: High
**Description**: Export generated resumes to PDF format for professional use.

**Functional Requirements:**
- **REQ-3.3.1-1**: System shall validate resume content exists before export
- **REQ-3.3.1-2**: System shall provide file save dialog
- **REQ-3.3.1-3**: System shall use .pdf extension by default
- **REQ-3.3.1-4**: System shall format PDF with professional layout
- **REQ-3.3.1-5**: System shall include all resume sections in PDF
- **REQ-3.3.1-6**: System shall use readable fonts and appropriate spacing
- **REQ-3.3.1-7**: System shall provide success/error feedback

### 3.4 User Interface

#### 3.4.1 Main Window Interface
**Priority**: High
**Description**: Provide intuitive and visually appealing user interface.

**Functional Requirements:**
- **REQ-3.4.1-1**: Window size shall be 950x750 pixels
- **REQ-3.4.1-2**: Interface shall use specified color theme (pink, purple, lavender, mint)
- **REQ-3.4.1-3**: All text shall be clearly readable against background
- **REQ-3.4.1-4**: Interface shall be scrollable for smaller screens
- **REQ-3.4.1-5**: Buttons shall have hover effects
- **REQ-3.4.1-6**: Input fields shall have clear labels

#### 3.4.2 Mode Selection
**Priority**: High
**Description**: Allow users to select between Template and AI generation modes.

**Functional Requirements:**
- **REQ-3.4.2-1**: System shall provide radio buttons for mode selection
- **REQ-3.4.2-2**: Template mode shall be selected by default
- **REQ-3.4.2-3**: Selection shall be clearly visible
- **REQ-3.4.2-4**: System shall indicate if AI mode is unavailable

#### 3.4.3 Status Feedback
**Priority**: Medium
**Description**: Provide real-time status updates to users.

**Functional Requirements:**
- **REQ-3.4.3-1**: System shall display current operation status
- **REQ-3.4.3-2**: Status colors shall indicate state (green=ready, blue=processing, red=error)
- **REQ-3.4.3-3**: Error messages shall be clear and actionable
- **REQ-3.4.3-4**: Success messages shall confirm operation completion

