## 6. Non-Functional Requirements

### 6.1 Performance Requirements

#### 6.1.1 Response Time
- **Template Generation**: Maximum 2 seconds
- **AI Model Loading**: Maximum 60 seconds (first time only)
- **AI Generation**: 10-30 seconds (varies by hardware)
- **Database Operations**: Maximum 1 second
- **PDF Export**: Maximum 5 seconds
- **UI Responsiveness**: Immediate feedback (<100ms) for all interactions

#### 6.1.2 Throughput
- Support generation of up to 100 resumes per session
- Database shall handle up to 1000 saved records without performance degradation

#### 6.1.3 Resource Usage
- **Memory**: Maximum 2 GB RAM (4 GB with AI model loaded)
- **CPU**: Minimal CPU usage during idle
- **Disk I/O**: Efficient database operations
- **Storage Growth**: Database file grows approximately 1 KB per saved resume

### 6.2 Security Requirements

#### 6.2.1 Data Privacy
- **REQ-6.2.1-1**: All user data shall remain local to the user's computer
- **REQ-6.2.1-2**: No data shall be transmitted over network
- **REQ-6.2.1-3**: No telemetry or tracking shall be implemented
- **REQ-6.2.1-4**: Database shall be stored in application directory

#### 6.2.2 Data Integrity
- **REQ-6.2.2-1**: Database operations shall use transactions
- **REQ-6.2.2-2**: System shall validate data before storage
- **REQ-6.2.2-3**: Corrupted data shall not crash the application

### 6.3 Reliability Requirements

#### 6.3.1 Availability
- **REQ-6.3.1-1**: Application shall start successfully 99.9% of the time
- **REQ-6.3.1-2**: Application shall function without internet connectivity

#### 6.3.2 Error Handling
- **REQ-6.3.2-1**: System shall catch and handle all exceptions
- **REQ-6.3.2-2**: Error messages shall be user-friendly
- **REQ-6.3.2-3**: Application shall not crash on invalid input
- **REQ-6.3.2-4**: Failed operations shall not corrupt database

#### 6.3.3 Recovery
- **REQ-6.3.3-1**: Database shall maintain integrity after crash
- **REQ-6.3.3-2**: Partial operations shall be rolled back on failure

### 6.4 Maintainability Requirements

#### 6.4.1 Code Quality
- **REQ-6.4.1-1**: Code shall follow PEP 8 Python style guidelines
- **REQ-6.4.1-2**: Functions shall have docstrings
- **REQ-6.4.1-3**: Code shall be modular and organized in packages

#### 6.4.2 Documentation
- **REQ-6.4.2-1**: README shall provide installation instructions
- **REQ-6.4.2-2**: Code shall include inline comments for complex logic
- **REQ-6.4.2-3**: SRS document shall be maintained and updated

### 6.5 Portability Requirements

#### 6.5.1 Platform Independence
- **REQ-6.5.1-1**: Application shall run on Windows, macOS, and Linux
- **REQ-6.5.1-2**: UI shall adapt to different screen sizes
- **REQ-6.5.1-3**: File paths shall use OS-independent conventions

#### 6.5.2 Compatibility
- **REQ-6.5.2-1**: Application shall work with Python 3.12+
- **REQ-6.5.2-2**: PDF output shall be compatible with standard PDF readers

### 6.6 Usability Requirements

#### 6.6.1 Ease of Use
- **REQ-6.6.1-1**: Users shall generate first resume within 5 minutes
- **REQ-6.6.1-2**: Interface shall be intuitive without training
- **REQ-6.6.1-3**: All buttons shall have descriptive labels
- **REQ-6.6.1-4**: Error messages shall guide users to resolution

#### 6.6.2 Aesthetics
- **REQ-6.6.2-1**: Interface shall use consistent color scheme
- **REQ-6.6.2-2**: Fonts shall be readable at default size
- **REQ-6.6.2-3**: Layout shall be visually balanced
- **REQ-6.6.2-4**: Buttons shall provide visual feedback on hover

#### 6.6.3 Accessibility
- **REQ-6.6.3-1**: Text shall have sufficient contrast with background
- **REQ-6.6.3-2**: Interface shall be keyboard-navigable
- **REQ-6.6.3-3**: Font size shall be readable without magnification

