## 7. Data Requirements

### 7.1 Database Schema

#### 7.1.1 Resumes Table (Input Data)
```sql
CREATE TABLE resumes (
    id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,
    name TEXT NOT NULL,
    email TEXT,
    phone TEXT,
    education TEXT,
    skills TEXT,
    experience TEXT,
    created_at TEXT NOT NULL,
    updated_at TEXT NOT NULL
);
```

**Fields:**
- `id`: Unique identifier (auto-generated)
- `name`: User's full name (required)
- `email`: Contact email address (optional)
- `phone`: Contact phone number (optional)
- `education`: Educational background (optional)
- `skills`: List of skills (optional)
- `experience`: Work experience details (optional)
- `created_at`: Timestamp of record creation (ISO format)
- `updated_at`: Timestamp of last update (ISO format)

#### 7.1.2 Generated Resumes Table
```sql
CREATE TABLE generated_resumes (
    id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,
    title TEXT NOT NULL,
    content TEXT NOT NULL,
    mode TEXT,
    created_at TEXT NOT NULL
);
```

**Fields:**
- `id`: Unique identifier (auto-generated)
- `title`: User-provided resume title (required)
- `content`: Complete resume text (required)
- `mode`: Generation mode ("Template" or "AI")
- `created_at`: Timestamp of creation (ISO format)

### 7.2 Data Validation

#### 7.2.1 Input Validation Rules
- **Name**: Must not be empty for save operations
- **Email**: No format validation (optional field)
- **Phone**: No format validation (optional field)
- **Text Fields**: No maximum length restrictions
- **Title**: Must not be empty when saving generated resume

#### 7.2.2 Data Sanitization
- No SQL injection protection needed (using parameterized queries)
- Special characters preserved in all text fields
- Line breaks and formatting preserved

### 7.3 Data Storage

#### 7.3.1 Database File
- **Filename**: resumes.db
- **Location**: Application root directory
- **Format**: SQLite 3
- **Encoding**: UTF-8

#### 7.3.2 PDF Files
- **Format**: PDF 1.4 or higher
- **Location**: User-selected directory
- **Naming**: User-provided filename with .pdf extension

### 7.4 Data Backup and Recovery
- **REQ-7.4-1**: Users responsible for backing up resumes.db
- **REQ-7.4-2**: Database file is portable (can be copied)
- **REQ-7.4-3**: No automatic backup mechanism provided

