### 8.4 Template Generation Algorithm

The template mode uses rule-based text generation:
1. Extract key information from input fields
2. Format name and contact information as header
3. Parse and bullet-point education entries
4. Format skills as comma-separated list or bullets
5. Parse and structure experience entries
6. Apply consistent formatting and spacing
7. Add section headers and visual separators

### 8.5 AI Generation Process

The AI mode uses FLAN-T5 model:
1. Load pre-trained model (google/flan-t5-small)
2. Construct prompt from user input
3. Tokenize prompt for model input
4. Generate text using model inference
5. Decode and format generated content
6. Combine sections into complete resume
7. Apply post-processing for consistency

### 8.6 Glossary

- **Resume**: A document containing a summary of a person's qualifications and experience
- **Template Mode**: Predefined format-based generation approach
- **AI Mode**: Machine learning model-based generation approach
- **Collection**: Stored set of generated resumes
- **Input Data**: User's personal information for resume generation
- **SQLite**: Serverless, file-based relational database
- **Tkinter**: Python's standard GUI toolkit
- **PDF Export**: Converting resume to Portable Document Format
- **FLAN-T5**: Google's fine-tuned language model for text generation
- **Transformers**: Hugging Face library for natural language processing

### 8.7 Future Enhancements (Out of Scope for v1.0)

- Multiple resume templates
- Custom color theme selection
- Export to Word format (.docx)
- Grammar and spell checking
- Resume scoring and suggestions
- LinkedIn profile import
- Multi-language support
- Resume comparison feature
- Cloud sync (optional)
- Mobile companion app

### 8.8 Known Limitations

1. AI mode requires significant RAM (4-8 GB)
2. AI model download may take time on first use
3. No built-in spell checker
4. Single window interface (no multi-document support)
5. Limited PDF formatting options
6. No resume templates beyond default
7. No undo/redo functionality for generated resumes
8. No print preview before PDF export

### 8.9 Testing Requirements

#### 8.9.1 Unit Testing
- Test database CRUD operations
- Test resume generation functions
- Test PDF export functionality
- Test input validation

#### 8.9.2 Integration Testing
- Test UI with database operations
- Test UI with resume engine
- Test end-to-end resume generation workflow

#### 8.9.3 User Acceptance Testing
- Verify usability with target users
- Confirm resume quality meets expectations
- Validate PDF output is professional
- Test on multiple operating systems

#### 8.9.4 Performance Testing
- Measure generation time under various loads
- Test with large text inputs
- Verify memory usage remains within limits

